Why is x an array in the softmax function?
text: Sorry if this sounds dumb, I'm new to ML. So basically, if the softmax function is "e ^ (x - max(x)) / sum(e^(x - max(x))", I understand what e is, but then what's x? I keep seeing people make x an array, but shouldn't it just be a single number or float? Isn't that what the output would be of the summation formula? Thanks.

I was bored and tired of creating subprocess wrappers for lots of projects, so I made this.

The implementation is fairly naive and a bit slow, but it works well in my testing.

Might be a bit useless, but it was a fun and somewhat interesting project.
